# Preserve Delete Functionality

When programming, do not remove or disable delete buttons and APIs. Users should be able to delete data (e.g. remove people from tours, delete schedule items).

## AI never deletes on its own

- Do not proactively suggest or implement deletions
- Do not remove data, records, or functionality unless the user explicitly tells you to delete
- When the user explicitly asks you to delete something, follow their instruction

## Do not remove when refactoring

- Delete buttons in the UI
- DELETE API endpoints
- Any code that allows users to remove work data

## User-initiated deletions are allowed

Users (admin/editor) may delete traveling group members, schedule items, and other work data. The APIs should support these actions.
